               <p>BARNARD WILLIAM MORELAND. I am a <rs id="t18250915-267-viclabel1433" type="occupation">wax-chandler</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-267-victim1346 t18250915-267-viclabel1433"></join>, and live in Oxford-street. On the 14th of August I was in Nassau-street - a person named Woodward came and asked if I had lost my handkerchief; I felt, and found it was gone - he then shewed it to me; I had had it not ten minutes before.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. The gentleman said at the office that it was not his property. Witness. No - I expressed no doubt about it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-267-person1347">
                  JOHN 
                  WOODWARD
               <interp inst="t18250915-267-person1347" type="surname" value="WOODWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-267-person1347" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-267-person1347" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in <placeName id="t18250915-267-crimeloc1434">Mortimer-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-267-crimeloc1434" type="placeName" value="Mortimer-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-267-crimeloc1434" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-267-off1431 t18250915-267-crimeloc1434"></join> - I saw the prisoner and another lad following this gentleman, for about one hundred and fifty yards - I then saw them separate suddenly; I took the prisoner, and found the handkerchief between his trousers and his jacket. When I said I would take him he threw himself down, and began to kick; I took him up, and carried him to Nassau-street, where I found the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I had found it half an hour before.</p>
               <p>JOHN WOODWARD. I followed him all the way up Mortimer-street, and am quite sure he did not pick it up.</p>
               <p>
